widgets_values: Twilight over the city, the horizon painted in deep reds and purples. From behind clustered rooftops, a giant man crouches low, his shadow spilling across the buildings. nodes.title: Select samplers for the preferred model workflow.

widgets_values:
The recommended step count for lightx is 6!

For a quick preview, you can use a lower number like 2 — the animation should still remain consistent.

Higher steps can result in a worse quality of the actor.

Download the largest possible GGUF model that is compatible with your card here:

[https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.1_14B_VACE-GGUF/tree/main](https://huggingface.co/QuantStack/Wan2.1_14B_VACE-GGUF/tree/main)

- Wan2.1_14B_VACE-Q5_1.gguf
- Wan2.1_14B_VACE-Q6_K.gguf
- Wan2.1_14B_VACE-Q8_0.gguf


📁 ComfyUI/models/unet

When setting up the start frame there different advantages of each option.
- Option 1 = If you want as much adherence to the background image.
- Option 2 = If you don"t want thje actor to appear in the shot right away, but make them enter the frame.
- Option 3 = If you want WAN to generate the overall image through describing it through the textprompt.
